# ======================================================================
#                BillTea Master Environment Configurations
# ======================================================================
#
# This project consists of three distinct components:
#   1. server/ (NestJS Backend API)
#   2. client/ (Next.js Web Frontend)
#   3. mobile/ (Expo/React Native Mobile App)
#
# Each component requires its own local environment file (.env) to run.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. NestJS Backend Server (server/.env)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Create a 'server/.env' file containing:
#
# PORT=5000
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:YOUR_PASSWORD_HERE@localhost:5432/BillTea?schema=public"
# JWT_SECRET=YOUR_JWT_SECRET_HERE
# JWT_ACCESS_EXPIRES_IN=15m
# JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRES_IN=30d
# UPLOAD_DIR=./uploads
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. Next.js Web Frontend (client/.env)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Create a 'client/.env' file containing:
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api/v1
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. Expo Mobile App (mobile/.env)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# The 'run_android.bat' and 'run_android.sh' scripts will automatically 
# detect your local network IP and generate this file.
# If creating manually, create a 'mobile/.env' containing:
#
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://<YOUR_LOCAL_NETWORK_IP_ADDRESS>:5000/api/v1
#
# ======================================================================
